node.title: No sign of man believed to have been taken by shark at Fremantle beach
node.alt: A bunch of yellow flowers placed at Port Beach after a shark attack.
node.description: A number of beaches around Fremantle remain closed as the search continues for a 57-year-old man believed to have been taken by a shark on Saturday.
node.content:
["There is still no sign of a middle-aged man believed to have been taken\u00a0by a shark at Port Beach in Western Australia on Saturday morning.", "Authorities have confirmed they are still\u00a0searching for the\u00a057-year-old father, who witnesses say was taken by up to two sharks while swimming at the Fremantle beach.", "Police believe the man was a regular at Port Beach.", "The attack was witnessed by a group of young people on a boat nearby who alerted emergency services straight away.", "They were also praised for urging others to get out of the water.", "Boats from a number of emergency services including Water Police and Marine Rescue are involved in the search.", "Surf lifesavers on jet skis are also scouring the area.", "", "
Mobile phone vision captures what appears to be a dorsal fin
", "Beaches in the area remain closed and lifesavers are conducting patrols to make sure people keep out of the water.", "Members of a local swimming group The Polar Bears gathered near the beach this morning for their regular swim, only to find it closed.", "One of the members who walked down to the beach despite the closure signs told the ABC he was threatened by authorities with a $1,000 fine.", "", "
The sea search was paused overnight, but resumed\u00a0this morning.(ABC News)
"]
